CAPE TOWN – South Africa's Kevin Anderson won through to the Madrid Open semifinals on Friday after defeating Serbia's Dusan Lajovic 7-6 (7-3) 3-6 6-3 in two hours and 12 minutes on the Manolo Santana Court in Spain. This was Anderson's first career win in a Masters 1000 quarterfinal round. Up to now, he has gone 10 quarterfinals winless in Masters 1000 competition. 11th time lucky...
		
		A relief for @KAndersonATP - into his first Masters 1000 semi-final 7-6(3) 3-6 6-3 over Lajovic.#MMOPEN pic.twitter.com/IhFxyuloCI READ: Kevin Anderson holds eighth place in ATP singles rankings Playing on the Manolo Santana claycourt, Anderson cracked 35 winners to Lajovic's 20 in the match. Anderson will meet the winner of the Rafael Nadal - Dominic Thiem quarterfinal later on Friday. African News Agency